abstract: In its first year Google Ventures invested in 10 start-ups, and it plans to expand its reach.
snippet: In its first year Google Ventures invested in 10 start-ups, and it plans to expand its reach.
lead_paragraph: Google has been throwing money around the last few days. It bought a start-up called BumpTop, invested in wind farms and, on Monday, announced its 10th venture investment and some details about its year-old venture capital fund.

headline.main: Google’s Venture Fund Steps Up the Pace

abstract: In a blog post, Google said it had invested $38.8 million in two North Dakota wind farms, part of a larger push by its expanding venture capital unit.
